12.content:
The world of beer is rich and diverse, and recognizing and evaluating different beer styles requires expertise and training. In this article, we will explore the Beer Judge Certification Program (BJCP) as a pivotal organization in the beer world. We'll delve into its origin, structure, judge training, competition organization, certification process, and the significance of BJCP in enhancing beer quality. Certification through BJCP is not just a recognition of expertise but also a contribution to the development of beer culture.
&nbsp;  
&nbsp;  
![bjcp-naslovna.png](https://udruzenje-kucnih-pivara-srbije.s3.eu-central-1.amazonaws.com/bjcp_naslovna_7699bf68d5.png)
&nbsp;  
**1. Origin and Mission of BJCP**

The BJCP, founded in 1985, is a non-profit organization with the mission of standardizing and improving the tasting and evaluation of beer globally. It has evolved into a respected body that trains and certifies beer judges across different countries.
&nbsp;  
**2. Structure and Organization**

BJCP has a well-defined structure encompassing various levels of certification. From lower levels like BJCP Registered Judge to intermediate levels like Certified Beer Judge, up to the highest levels such as National and Master Judge, the program provides a progressive certification system.
&nbsp;  
**3. Training and Education**

One of BJCP's key aspects is the training and education of judges. The program offers detailed guidelines for understanding and evaluating different beer styles. Judges undergo thorough training covering technical aspects of beer, diverse styles, and quality assessment.
&nbsp;  
**4. Organization of Competitions**

BJCP plays a crucial role in organizing and overseeing beer competitions worldwide. Certified judges are tasked with evaluating various beer samples based on strict criteria, contributing to standardized judging and providing constructive feedback to beer producers.
&nbsp;  
**5. Certification Process**

Becoming a BJCP certified judge requires dedication, training, and experience. Candidates must pass a written exam covering theoretical knowledge about different beer styles, production processes, and quality assessment. Additionally, candidates go through a practical certification process, judging real beers at competitions.
&nbsp;  
**6. Significance of BJCP Certification**

Certification by BJCP is not merely a recognition of expertise but also a contribution to the brewing community. Certified judges play a key role in improving beer quality and fostering innovation in the brewing industry. Moreover, they provide valuable feedback to beer producers to enhance their skills and create exceptional beers.
&nbsp;  
&nbsp;  
**Conclusion**

The Beer Judge Certification Program is more than just a certification; it is a journey that opens doors to expertise and enjoyment in the world of beer. For those passionate about beer, becoming a certified judge through BJCP is not only a personal achievement but also a contribution to the development and promotion of beer culture. All additional information can be found on the official [BJCP website](https://www.bjcp.org/)
&nbsp;  
![bjcp-ocenjivanje-3.jpeg](https://udruzenje-kucnih-pivara-srbije.s3.eu-central-1.amazonaws.com/bjcp_ocenjivanje_3_d2c9e0169d.jpeg)


&nbsp;  
Author: [SvaRog BRu](https://www.pivari.rs/members/en/SvaRog-BRu)

